This Endenture, Made this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">27 day of August in the year of our Lord one thousand eight hundred and four</TIMEX>
BETWEEN <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William H. Hamlin</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esq.</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX> in the action hereinafter mentioned, of the Town of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Canandaigua</ENAMEX> in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Intario</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>,
of the first part, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Albert Proper</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of South Bristol</ENAMEX> in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX>, do
of the second part,
bered, At a Special
Term of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">County Court</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Ontario</ENAMEX>
held at <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Canandaigua</ENAMEX>
day of <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">July one thousand eight hundred</TIMEX> and Lowr it was, among other things, ordered, adjudged and decreed by the
and transaction then pending in the <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Court</ENAMEX>, between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mary H. Worthington</ENAMEX>, as <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">executrix</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">last will
and testament</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Emily Howell</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.rel">deceased</ENAMEX>, as <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">Plaintiff</ENAMEX>, and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Julia Quinin</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Jennie Quire</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mary R. Cotter</ENAMEX>, as <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">general guardian</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Jennie Quinn</ENAMEX>, an <ENAMEX TYPE="AGE">infant</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Albert J. Renoldson</ENAMEX>,
as temporary <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">guardian</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Jennie Quirin</ENAMEX>, an <ENAMEX TYPE="AGE">infant</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Albert J. Renddson</ENAMEX>, as <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">adminis-
=trator</ENAMEX> of the goods, chattles and credits of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Thomas Quinn</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.rel">deceased</ENAMEX> and also as
<ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">administrator</ENAMEX> with the will annexed of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Alta M. Quinn</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.rel">deceased</ENAMEX>, as <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">defendants</ENAMEX>
That all and singular the premises described in a mortgage executed by said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas Quinn</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Alto M. Quinn</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX>
To <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Emily Howell</ENAMEX>, late of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Canandaigua</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Ontario County</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">N. Y.</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.rel">Decd</ENAMEX>.
and recorded in <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Ontario County Clerk's Office</ENAMEX> in Liber 186 <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">of Mortgages</ENAMEX> at page 145 and being the same premises mentioned in the complaint in
said action, and in said judgment described, or such part thereof as is sufficient to discharge the mortgage
debt, the expenses of the sale and costs of
in said action, and which might be sold separately without material injury to the parties interested, be sold at public auction, according to the Law and practice of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Court</ENAMEX>
by and under the direction of the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William H. Hamlin</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="TITLE">Esq.</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> was appointed a <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX> in said action and to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">whom</ENAMEX> it was
referred by the said judgment,
among other things to make such sale; that the said sale be
made in the County where the said mortgaged premises, or the greater part thereof are situated; that the said <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX> give public notice of the time and place of such sale, according to
the course and practice of <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Court</ENAMEX>, and that any of the parties in said action might become a purchaser or purchasers on such sale, that the said <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX>
execute to the purchaser or purchasers of the said mortgaged premises, or such part or parts thereof as shall be sold, a good and sufficient deed or deeds of conveyance for the same.
and pay tax, assessments or water rates which were lins upon the property 
sold, etc.
and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Gilbereas</ENAMEX>, The said <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX>, in pursuance of the order and judgment of the <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">said Court</ENAMEX>
did on the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">27th
August one thousand eight hundred and four</TIMEX> sell at public auction, at the front on west also of the <ENAMEX TYPE="STRUCTURE">Court House</ENAMEX>
in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Canandaigua</ENAMEX>, the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>
the premises in the said order and judgment mentioned, due notice of the time and place of such sale being first given, pursuant to the said judgment
at which sale the premises hereinafter described were fairly struck off to the said party of the second part for the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Eight Hundred Fifty
five Dollars</NUMEX> ( <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">$855.00</NUMEX>)
that being the highest sum bidden for the same, and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">he</ENAMEX> being the highest bidder therefor.
How this <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX> Ulitnesseth. That the said <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX>, the party of the first part to these presents, in order to carry into effect the sale so made by <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">him</ENAMEX> as aforesaid,
in pursuance of the order and judgment of said Court, and in conformity to the Statute in such case made and provided, and also in consideration of the premises
and of the said sum of money so bidden as aforesaid having been first duly paid by the said party of the second part, the receipt whereof is hereby acknowledged, hath bargained and
sold, and by these presents doth grant and convey unto the said party of the second part, all the right, title, and interest which the and
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas Querin</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Alto M. Quinn</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX>, mortgagors aforesaid, had at the time of
the execution or recording of said mortgage, it being <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">their</ENAMEX> interest in said premises 
which was so sold and is hereby conveyed, in and to
All that Tract or Parcel of Land, situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of South Ruston</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX>, and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of 
New York</ENAMEX>, being <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one hundred</NUMEX> acres off the north part of Lot No. fifty ( 50) south of the con-
ter line, and bounded as follows; North, east, and west by the lines of the lot and on 
the south by a line drawn parallel with the north line, and so far distant there 
from as to include said <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one hundred</NUMEX> acres. Being the same premises conveyed 
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas Luirin</ENAMEX> by the <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">widow</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Oliver Phelps</ENAMEX> by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">September 
first 1875</TIMEX>, and recorded the same day in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Ontario County</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Clerk's office</ENAMEX> in Liber 
158 of Deeds at page 29.
LIBER 228.
5 9 5
Also all that other tract or parcel of land situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">town of South
Bristol</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Ontario</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, being <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">sixty four</NUMEX> acres of 
land on the south side of Lot No. Fifty-one ( 51) south of the center line, and
adjoining the above land, being the smitherly part of said Lot <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty-one</NUMEX> ( 5)
in the <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Phelps</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Gorham Purchase</ENAMEX>, in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE.notgpe">Range four, township eight</ENAMEX>, south of 
the center line, and being the same premises conveyed to said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Thomas Lunn</ENAMEX>
by <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">H.B. Ferguson</ENAMEX>, then <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Treasurer</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Ontario County</ENAMEX>, by deed dated <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">October
13th. 1881</TIMEX> and recorded on the same day in <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Ontario County</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Clerk</ENAMEX><ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">'s office</ENAMEX> in
<ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Liber 110 of Deeds</ENAMEX>, at pages 75.
To have and to bold. All and singular the premises above mentioned and described, and hereby conveyed
unto the said party of the
Second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever
in <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Glitness Elbereof</ENAMEX>. The said party of the first part, <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX> as aforesaid, hath hereunto set <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> hand and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
Sealed and Delivered in the Presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William H. Hamlin</ENAMEX>, ℗
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX>.
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, 
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">COUNTY OF Ontario</ENAMEX> 
On this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">2785 day of Amoust in the year one thousand nine hundred and four</TIMEX>
before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>.
the subscriber, personally appeared <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">William H. Hamlin</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Referee</ENAMEX> etc., of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Village of Canandaigua</ENAMEX> 
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> personally known to be the same person described in, and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the instrument, and acknowledged that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">he</ENAMEX> executed
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Mark S. Powell</ENAMEX>.
Affidavit Recorded <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">4 October 1951</TIMEX> in <ENAMEX TYPE="WORK_OF_ART">Liber 514 Deeds</ENAMEX> page 105 A true copy. Recorded this <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">9th day of September 1894</TIMEX>, at <TIMEX TYPE="TIME">235 o'clock P. M.</TIMEX> and examined.
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Huch</ENAMEX> as
</SBODY>
